This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with malware detection and classification, which is a crucial aspect of cybersecurity. The paper also utilizes social network analysis techniques to analyze the system call graph of malware families, which falls under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms for classification purposes also makes it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of network properties, which can be categorized under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a tool, which can be categorized under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
